<b>Poliqarp</b> is an <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../758/18938758.xml">
open source</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../023/4059023.xml">
search engine</link> designed to process the Polish Corpus created at the <link>
Institute of Computer Science</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../139/893139.xml">
Polish Academy of Sciences</link>.
<sec>
<st>
Features</st>

<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Custom <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../528/494528.xml">
query language</link>.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Two-level <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../717/25717.xml">
regular expressions</link></entry>
<entry level="2" type="bullet">

 operating at the level of characters in words</entry>
<entry level="2" type="bullet">

 operating at the level of words in statements/paragraphs</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Good performance</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Compact corpus representation (compared to similar projects)</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Portability across operating systems: <O wordnetid="106832680" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../297/6097297.xml">
Linux</link></O>
/<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../807/1223807.xml">
BSD</link>/<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../601/81601.xml">
Win32</link></entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Lack of portability across <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../026/43026.xml">
endiannes</link> (current release works only on little endian devices)</entry>
</list>
</p>

